            3. Assess: Scope of outage
            4. Declare: Disaster declared
            5. Notify: DR team activated

            Activation Phase 15-60 minutes:
            6. DNS: Update Route 53 to DR region
            7. S3: Verify replication current
            8. Catalog: Verify DR Glue Catalog
            9. EMR: Launch DR clusters
            10. Lambda: Deploy DR functions
            11. Step Functions: Deploy DR workflows
            12. Athena: Configure workgroups
            13. QuickSight: Point to DR dashboards
            14. Monitoring: Switch to DR CloudWatch

            Validation Phase 60-90 minutes:
            15. Data: Validate replicated data
            16. ETL: Run test pipeline
            17. Query: Execute test queries
            18. Dashboard: Verify QuickSight works
            19. Access: Test user authentication
            20. Permissions: Verify Lake Formation

            Go-Live Phase 90-120 minutes:
            21. Communication: Notify stakeholders
            22. Users: Grant access to DR
            23. Monitoring: Active alerting
            24. Support: War room active
            25. Documentation: Log all actions

            Steady State Phase:
            26. Monitor: All systems
            27. Optimize: Performance tuning
            28. Cleanup: Primary region when recovered
            29. Root cause: Post-mortem analysis
            30. Update: Runbooks with lessons learned

            RTO Achievement: 2-4 hours full recovery]

            DataLossScenario[Data Loss/Corruption Scenario

            Accidental Deletion:
            Impact: Critical table deleted

            Response:
            1. Immediate: Block further changes
            2. Assess: What was deleted, when
            3. S3 Versioning: Restore deleted objects
            4. Glue Catalog: Restore table metadata
            5. Validation: Verify data integrity
            6. Testing: Run quality checks
            7. Communication: Notify affected users
            8. Post-mortem: Review and prevent

            Recovery Time: 30-60 minutes
            Data Loss: 0 with versioning

            Data Corruption:
            Impact: Bad data in Silver zone

            Response:
            1. Identify: Corruption timeframe
            2. Quarantine: Mark bad partitions
            3. S3: Delete corrupted data
            4. Replay: Re-run ETL from Bronze
            5. Validation: Quality checks pass
            6. Replace: Swap in good data
            7. Notify: Downstream consumers
            8. Root cause: Fix bug in ETL

            Recovery Time: 2-4 hours
            Data Loss: Depends on checkpoints

            Ransomware Attack:
            Impact: Data encrypted/held hostage

            Response:
            1. Isolate: Cut network access
            2. Assess: Scope of encryption
            3. Restore: From S3 versioning
            4. Restore: From cross-region backups
            5. Rebuild: Catalog from backups
            6. Scan: Security assessment
            7. Harden: Enhanced security
            8. Report: Security incident

            Recovery Time: 4-8 hours
            Data Loss: Max 1 hour RPO]
        end

